      <bioghist>
         <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
         <p>John Butler (b. ca. 1670) was from King William County,
         Virginia.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>The deed was issued as an exhibit in an equity suit in
         Abbeville District, South Carolina, in 1815. In the deed dated
         20 July 1727, John Butler dictates ownership of his slaves
         upon his death.</p>
